 <!--hvy:expandable {}-->
  <!--hvy:expandable:stub {}-->

   <!--hvy:text {}-->
    ## Search / Filtering

  <!--hvy:expandable:content {}-->

   <!--hvy:xref-card {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0; padding-left: 0.5rem;","xrefTitle":"Search","xrefDetail":"Use search to highlight terms and navigate to them. Search results include a description provided by the containing components or sections.","xrefTarget":"search"}-->

   <!--hvy:xref-card {"css":"margin: 0.5rem 0; padding-left: 0.5rem;","xrefTitle":"Filtering","xrefDetail":"Filter to rearrange the document and show matching sections and components first.","xrefTarget":"filtering"}-->
<!--hvy: {"id":"section-4brwub","lock":false,"expanded":true,"highlight":false}-->
#! Styling

 <!--hvy:text {}-->
  # Styling

 <!--hvy:text {}-->
  Styling is done through CSS properties attached a component. You can edit this in advanced mode or by asking the AI to make styling changes.
<!--hvy: {"id":"advanced-editing","lock":false,"expanded":true,"highlight":false}-->
#! Advanced Editing

 <!--hvy:text {}-->
  # Advanced Editing

 <!--hvy:text {}-->
  You can choose between basic and advanced editing mode.
  
  Advanced editing mode reveals "Make Template" and "Meta" editing information.

 <!--hvy:text {}-->
  ### Templating and Fill-ins
  
  You can set up a template components and sections with the "Make Template" button. This makes a reproducible copy that will show up under the "Custom" section when adding components. You can select text and convert it to a fill-in, meaning in an edit mode one can simply click on the spot and enter text.
  
  ### Meta Information
  
  The document, sections, and components all have meta information. This includes placeholders for empty text, tags, a description for search, and more.
  
  ### Editor Only Components
  
  You can a component to be editor only. For example, you may want to display helpful hints on how to use a template, or run a script in editing mode only.
<!--hvy: {"id":"search","lock":false,"expanded":true,"highlight":false}-->
#! Search

 <!--hvy:text {}-->
  # Search

 <!--hvy:text {}-->
  You can search by word(s) by pressing the magnifying glass button or `cmd / ctrl + f.`
  
  The search term is highlighted and you can click results to get navigate to the entry.
  
  The description you see is provided by components via meta information.
<!--hvy: {"id":"filtering","lock":false,"expanded":true,"highlight":false}-->
#! Filtering

 <!--hvy:text {}-->
  # Filtering

 <!--hvy:text {}-->
  You can filter by word(s) by pressing the magnifying glass button or `cmd / ctrl + f.`
  
  There's two filter techniques.
  
  If shade is selected, sections / components without the term are shaded and may be displayed lower in the document.
  
  If hide is selected, then sections / components that do not match the term are not displayed.
